@startuml Exit Signal Trapping - Receive Crash Signals as Messages

title Exit Signal Trapping: Handle Linked Process Crashes as Mailbox Messages

participant "Proc B" as procB
participant "Proc B Mailbox" as mailboxB
participant "Message Loop" as loopB
participant "Trap Handler" as trapHandler
participant "Proc A" as procA

== Setup: Trap Exits ==

procB -> procB: trapExits(true)
note right of procB
  Signal handling mode enabled
  Exit signals delivered as messages
  (not immediate crash)
end note

== Normal Operation ==

procA -> procA: process normally

procB -> loopB: wait for messages
loopB -> loopB: ready for messages

== Proc A Crashes ==

procA -> procA: exception in handler
procA -> procA: lastError = exception
procA -> procA: exit message loop

note right of procA
  Linked to procB
  Crash callback fires
end note

== Exit Signal Delivery ==

procA -> procB: onCrash callback (bilateral link)
procB -> mailboxB: enqueue ExitSignal(procA, reason)
note right of mailboxB
  ExitSignal is a record:
  - from: Proc<S,M> procA
  - reason: Throwable exception
  Delivered as normal message
end note

== Signal Processing ==

loopB -> mailboxB: poll next message
mailboxB --> loopB: ExitSignal(procA, exception)

loopB -> trapHandler: handle(ExitSignal)
note right of trapHandler
  procB's message handler
  receives signal like any message
end note

alt Handle and Recover
  trapHandler -> trapHandler: log crash
  trapHandler -> trapHandler: spawn replacement
  trapHandler --> loopB: newState (recovery)
else Propagate Crash
  trapHandler -> procB: re-throw exception
  procB -> procB: exit message loop
  procB -> procB: crash propagates upward
end

== Key Difference ==

note over procB, procA
  WITHOUT trapExits(true):
  - Crash callback fires
  - procB.interrupt() is called
  - InterruptedException immediately
  - procB crashes (unless caught)
  - Cascading failure

  WITH trapExits(true):
  - Crash callback fires
  - ExitSignal enqueued to mailbox
  - procB continues running
  - Signal processed in next iteration
  - Can handle gracefully
end note

note right of procB
  procB can:
  1. Ignore signal (skip handling)
  2. Handle + recover (spawn replacement)
  3. Log + continue (monitoring)
  4. Deliberately propagate (re-throw)
end note
